#week-title("One", "The Achievement of the Plant Stone")

=== Core Teaching

The Plant Stone is the crowning achievement of the first year's work. It is
produced when the triple cohobated preparation — with all three principles
reunited and elevated — is sealed in a glass vessel and subjected to sustained
moderate heat over weeks or months.

The substance passes through color changes: black (*Nigredo*), grey, and
eventually toward white or redness. It arrives at a coherent, semi-solid or
solid state. This "stone" in the vegetable kingdom has the property of
attracting the essence, sulphur, and salt of other plants by simple immersion.

#doctrine[
  _"The Plant Stone is a coherent body in which the three principles have been
  truly unified, of far greater potency than any tincture, extract, or salt
  alone."_
  #align(right)[— TTAO curriculum]
]

=== Topics This Week

- Definition and properties of the Plant Stone
- The sealed vessel digestion protocol
- Monitoring color changes through the glass

#inner-work[
  *The Glimpse of Rubedo*

  The *Rubedo* (the Reddening) corresponds to the Philosopher's Stone in the
  mineral work. In Year One, we seek only glimpses. These confirm that the path
  is genuine.

  Reflect on your work this year. Have you had a moment — in meditation, in a
  vigil, or in the lab — where the work briefly felt transparent, whole, and
  warm? Record this glimpse in your journal.
]

